message: Hey, I know you're going through a lot right now, and it might feel like you're the only one dealing with this, but trust me, you're not. Everyone struggles sometimes, especially when things get tough. It's way more common than people think, and just because you're feeling down doesn't mean there's something wrong with you. We're all in this together, and I'm here for you.
reflection: I remember when I didn't make the basketball team in middle school, and I felt like the only one who wasn't good enough. Everyone else seemed so happy and skilled, and I felt like a total loser. But then I found out that a bunch of other kids who tried out didn't make it either, and it made me feel a little better. It's still disappointing, but knowing that I wasn't alone made it less awful.

message: Hey, I know you're going through a lot right now, but you're def not the only one. Everyone struggles sometimes, even if they don't show it. It's easy to feel like you're alone, but trust me, tons of other people your age are dealing with the same kinda stuff. We all got our own problems, so just remember that it's normal to feel how you're feeling, and you'll get through it.
reflection: Last year, I felt like I was the only one who wasn't excited about going back to school after lockdown. Everyone else seemed hyped to see their friends, but I was super anxious about being behind in all my classes and having to deal with crowds again. I felt like a total weirdo for not wanting things to go back to normal, but now I realize a lot of other kids were probably secretly stressed too. I just wish I knew that then, it would have made me feel less like I was the only one struggling.
takeaway: I guess the main thing I'm taking away is that it's okay to not be okay sometimes. And even though it feels like I'm the only one freaking out, probably other people are too, even if they don't show it.

message: Hey, I know you're going through a lot right now, and it might feel like you're the only one who feels this way, but you're not. Seriously, everyone struggles with stuff, especially at our age. It's just that people don't always talk about it, so it seems like you're alone, but trust me, you're not. We're all in this together, even if it doesn't always feel like it.
reflection: I remember when I didn't make the varsity team for basketball. I felt like total garbage and thought everyone else was just naturally good and I was the only one who sucked. But then I talked to some of the other kids who didn't make it and found out they felt the same way. Knowing that others felt just as bummed made me feel a little less alone and that it wasn't just a 'me' problem.
takeaway: That it's okay to feel bad sometimes, and it doesn't mean I'm a weirdo. It just means I'm a normal person going through stuff like everyone else. DONE

message: Hey, I know you're going through it right now, but you're def not the only one. Everyone struggles sometimes, especially with all the stuff we have to deal with. It might seem like you're alone, but trust me, tons of other people feel the same way. We can talk about it if you want.
reflection: I remember when I failed that math test last year. I thought everyone else was doing great, and I was the only one who didn't get it. It made me feel so stupid and alone, like I was just bad at everything. But thinking about it now, I bet a bunch of other people were struggling too, they just didn't show it. message: Hey, I know you're feeling like you're the only one going through this, but trust me, you're not. Everyone struggles sometimes, especially as a teen. It might seem like everyone else has it together, but they don't. We all have moments where we feel lost or overwhelmed, and it's totally normal. So don't beat yourself up about it, okay?
reflection: I remember when I didn't get into the school play last year. I felt like everyone else was talented and I was just a loser. It seemed like all my friends were so happy for each other, and I was the only one feeling left out and bummed. Thinking about it now, I'm sure other people who didn't get in were also feeling the same way, even if they didn't show it. Maybe it wasn't just me being untalented; maybe the others felt like a disappointment too.
takeaway: I guess I'll try to remember that just because I'm struggling doesn't mean I'm a weirdo or anything. Everyone has bad days, and it's probably more common than I think. So, like, chill out a little, ya know?

It's probably more common than I thought to feel excluded like that, and it probably doesn't mean I'm a loser after all.
